###  http://www.semanticweb.org/bionik/portion_of_material
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bionik/portion_of_material> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                        rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000040> ;
                                                        rdfs:comment "The class is introduced for householding purposes, such that all \"portion of\" classes can be subsumed under it." ;
                                                        <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A portion of material is a material entity such that its identity depends only on the atoms or molecules present (whatever is the larger unit present), irrespective of size, shape, structure or kind membership of the whole portion." .


